The paper proposes a novel method for training agents in reinforcement learning using shared knowledge, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves clustering input states semantically and selecting core experiences to be stored in a container, which relates to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions defining linguistic functions, which suggests the use of natural language processing (cs.CL).
